# Bookshelf Apps

Bookshelf Apps is a modular, responsive web application designed to help you manage your personal book collection. Easily add, mark as read/unread, and delete books from your list with a clean and accessible interface.

## Table of Contents  

- [Features](#features)
- [Project Structure](#project-structure)
- [Getting Started](#getting-started)
  - [Prerequisites](#prerequisites)
  - [Installation](#installation)
- [Usage](#usage)
- [Customization](#customization)
- [Contributing](#contributing)

## Features

- **Add Books:** Add new books to your collection using a user-friendly modal form.
- **Toggle Status:** Easily mark books as read or unread.
- **Persistent Storage:** Uses local storage to save your book data between sessions.
- **Responsive Design:** Optimized for both desktop and mobile viewing.
- **Accessible:** Designed with accessibility in mind, including proper labels and semantic HTML.

