## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- A modern web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Edge, Opera, etc.)
- An internet connection (to load external fonts and icon libraries)

### Installation

1. **Clone the Repository:**

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/muhammadfaizalalkindi/bookshelf-apps-vol.1.git
   ```

2. **Navigate to the Project Folder:**

   ```bash
   cd bookshelf-apps-vol.1
   ```

3. **Open the Application:**

   Open the `index.html` file in your preferred web browser.

## Usage

- **Adding a Book:**
  - Click the "Add" icon to open the modal.
  - Fill in the book details (title, author, and publication year).
  - Click "Save" to add the book to your collection.
  
- **Toggling Book Status:**
  - Use the action buttons on each book to mark it as read or unread.
  
- **Deleting a Book:**
  - Click the trash icon on the book item you wish to remove.

## Customization

- **Styling:**  
  Modify the `css/style.css` file to change colors, layouts, and other visual elements.

- **Functionality:**  
  Update the JavaScript logic in `js/main.js` and `js/storage.js` to customize how books are managed or stored.

